						               													<description>After years of receiving and listening to our customers from around the world and compiling untold pages of feedback we have produced a full revision of our Global War rules, map and added a lot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;New units include:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;middot;      Tank Destroyers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;middot;      Self-Propelled Artillery&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;middot;      Heavy Battleships&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;middot;      Heavy Carriers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;middot;      Fast Battleships&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;middot;      Battlecruisers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;middot;      Light Cruisers&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;middot;      FEC Gurkhas&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The revised map is very exciting.  We&amp;rsquo;ve continued to update place names and features to reflect historical accuracy.  To our map we have now printed air and naval bases, coastal artillery and fortifications onto the map directly.  You will also find new types of air bases as well as Major and Minor shipyards, Minor Ports, and Dockyards.   The railways now are designated as standard gauge (1,435mm) and broad gauge (1520mm and wider).   We&amp;rsquo;ve added deserts, and jungles, channel ports, and more!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We have also updated significantly the rules for convoy raiding and escorts and added many new rules, new technologies, and revised all the play aids and National Reference sheets for greater clarify and playability.   We have fixed some loop holes and added clarity and examples everywhere we could.  In short, this has been a community effort with people from many countries contributing their knowledge, time and experise for the love of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Global War is, and will continue to be the most expanded game of its time with some 30 expansions and counting already produced we will soon add linking games to 1946 and 1914 with a flurry of expansions for each.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
